.TH "iop_adma_alloc_chan_resources" 9 "iop_adma_alloc_chan_resources" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iop_adma_alloc_chan_resources \- returns the number of allocated descriptors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" iop_adma_alloc_chan_resources
.BI "(struct dma_chan *chan "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chan" 12
allocate descriptor resources for this channel
.SH "NOTE"
We keep the slots for 1 operation on iop_chan->chain at all times.  To
avoid deadlock, via async_xor, num_descs_in_pool must at a minimum be
greater than 2x the number slots needed to satisfy a device->max_xor
request.
